# 2026-04-18 19:13:56.782574
+Use peer mode.
+
+Design a local AI workstation architecture for architecture, design, documentation, and research work.
+
+Constraints:
+- registry-driven MCP server catalogue
+- multiple specialist agents with controlled server access
+- local workspace retrieval
+- SharePoint / OneDrive retrieval
+- interactive CLI
+- heuristic routing for agent selection
+- review off by default
+- peer transcript visible in the CLI
+
+Please let the peers debate:
+- whether orchestration should stay mostly in main.py or be split further into modules
+- whether prompts and behavioural instructions should live in code or in external text files
+- how much autonomy the router should have versus explicit user control
+- how peer transcript visibility should work without overwhelming the CLI
+
+Final output:
+- show the peer conversation
+- then give a refined recommended architecture and rationale

